hopobject.body: I've just graduated drugs-in-london.skyrock.com Although Obama's speech wandered from policy specifics to more general themes, it was clear he was trying to let the world know he acknowledges missteps, such as working to balance security concerns with privacy concerns with regard to revelations about U.S. intelligence gathering and failure to impose democracy in Iraq through military means. He also tried to strike a leadership tone, trying to push countries into supporting U.S. goals – such as in Syria – despite their reluctance.
